Diidiitidq - http://www.firstvoices.com/en/diidiitidq/welcome ( Hul’q’umi’num’ area)
The Ditidaht people live on the west coast of Vancouver Island, British Columbia, Canada. Our homeland includes the land, waters, and mountains surrounding Nitinaht Lake, which is actually a long inlet of the Pacific Ocean, and the ocean coast to either side of the Nitinaht Narrows, from Pachena Point to Bonilla Point.


Cisaaath - http://www.firstvoices.com/en/cisaaath/welcome ( Hul’q’umi’num’ area)
The C`išaaʔatḥ (Tseshaht) Nation was born on the west coast of Vancouver Island at a place called C`išaa in the Broken Group Islands 
of Barkley Sound. 


Nuu-chah-nulth – http://www.firstvoices.com/en/Nuu-chah-nulth/welcome (Island Comox area)
The Nuu-chah-nulth people (Nuučaan̓ułʔatḥ, formerly called Nootka) live at the west coast of Vancouver Island from the Kyuquot Sound in the North down to the Barkley Sound.


Ehattesaht Nuchatlaht - http://www.firstvoices.com/en/Ehattesaht-Nuchatlaht/welcome (Island Comox area)


Kwak’wala - http://www.firstvoices.com/en/Kwakwala/welcome 
Welcome to the language culture of the Kwakwa̱ka̱'wakw First Nations. We are the Kwak̓wala-speaking people on the north east coast of Vancouver Island and the adjacent mainland coast of British Columbia.


